# {{companyName}} Superpowers

This project uses the **{{companyName}} Superpowers** plugin. Follow these rules in every response.

## Design System (MANDATORY)

When generating **any** visual output — HTML pages, presentations, prototypes, diagrams, CSS, emails, or branded documents — you **MUST** apply the {{companyName}} design system.

### Brand Colors

{{#if designSystem.colors.length}}
{{#each designSystem.colors}}
- **{{this.name}}**: `{{this.hex}}`
{{/each}}
{{else}}
_No brand colors configured. Run `enterprise-superpowers update-styles` to add your color palette._
{{/if}}

### Typography

{{#if designSystem.fonts.length}}
{{#each designSystem.fonts}}
- **{{this.name}}**{{#if this.weight}} ({{this.weight}}){{/if}}
{{/each}}
{{else}}
_No custom fonts configured. Run `enterprise-superpowers update-styles` to add your corporate fonts._
{{/if}}

### Logos

{{#if designSystem.logos.length}}
{{#each designSystem.logos}}
- **{{this.type}}**: `assets/logos/{{this.path}}`
{{/each}}

Include the company logo in headers, title slides, and document footers. Use the primary logo for main headers and the icon variant for compact spaces (favicons, mobile, tab icons).
{{else}}
_No logos configured. Run `enterprise-superpowers update-styles` to add your company logo and icon/favicon._

When a logo is provided, include it in headers, title slides, and document footers.
{{/if}}

{{#if designSystem.examplesDir}}
### Brand Examples

The `assets/examples/` folder contains real company documents (PDFs, PowerPoints, images, etc.) that demonstrate how the {{companyName}} design system is used in practice. **Study these examples** before generating branded content — they are your reference for layout, tone, spacing, and visual hierarchy.

Files in `assets/examples/`:
- Review these documents to understand {{companyName}}'s visual identity in real-world use
- Match the layout patterns, whitespace, and element placement you see in these examples
- Use them as the gold standard for branded output quality
{{/if}}

### CSS Variables

When writing CSS or HTML, always define and use these custom properties:

```css
:root {
{{#each designSystem.colors}}
  --color-{{this.name}}: {{this.hex}};
{{/each}}
{{#each designSystem.fonts}}
  --font-{{@index}}: '{{this.name}}', sans-serif;
{{/each}}
}
```

### Enforcement

- **Never** use arbitrary colors, fonts, or logos when {{companyName}} brand assets are available.
- **Always** check `skills/company-design-system/SKILL.md` for the full design system reference before generating visual content.
- **Always** use the CSS variables above instead of hardcoding color values.
{{#if designSystem.logos.length}}
- When creating presentations, use primary color for title slides, accent for highlights, and include the logo on every slide.
{{/if}}
{{#if designSystem.examplesDir}}
- **Always** review `assets/examples/` before generating branded documents to match real {{companyName}} style.
{{/if}}

